.TH "drm_dp_mst_dpcd_read" 9 "drm_dp_mst_dpcd_read" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_dp_mst_dpcd_read \- read a series of bytes from the DPCD via sideband
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" drm_dp_mst_dpcd_read
.BI "(struct drm_dp_aux *aux "  ","
.BI "unsigned int offset "  ","
.BI "void *buffer "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "aux" 12
Fake sideband AUX CH
.IP "offset" 12
address of the (first) register to read
.IP "buffer" 12
buffer to store the register values
.IP "size" 12
number of bytes in \fIbuffer\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Performs the same functionality for remote devices via
sideband messaging as \fBdrm_dp_dpcd_read\fP does for local
devices via actual AUX CH.
.SH "RETURN"
Number of bytes read, or negative error code on failure.
